 Baylor Scott & White Logo
Baylor Scott & White Health is a healthcare system based in Dallas, Texas, United States. Formed in 2013 from the merger of Scott & White Health with Baylor Healthcare System, it became the largest non-profit healthcare system in Texas, and one of the largest in the country. Its network contains over 50 hospitals and more than 800 patient care sites, including Baylor University Medical Center in Dallas, Baylor Scott & White Medical Center – Temple, and Baylor Scott & White Medical Center – Plano.
